FAQs
What are the top universities to study medicine in Warsaw?

The Medical University of Warsaw is among the top universities for medical studies in Warsaw.
Do I need to know Polish to study medicine in Warsaw?

Most medical programs at the Medical University of Warsaw are taught in English, but learning basic Polish can be beneficial for daily life and clinical practice.
What documents are needed to apply for a medical program in Warsaw?

You will need academic transcripts, proof of English language proficiency, letters of recommendation, a personal statement, a valid passport, and passport-sized photographs.
